<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/127680572-cm">CM</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">NO.<br/><br/>Before I read it, I thought &quot;How bad could the rape scene be?&quot;. Well, besides the rape itself it was horrible because it told the reader that it&apos;s <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">NO.<br /><br />Before I read it, I thought "How bad could the rape scene be?". Well, besides the rape itself it was horrible because it told the reader that it's okay to rape because the woman will immediately forgive you and decide to spend the rest of her life with you.<br /><br />So unless the message you want a 12 year old boy to learn is that it's okay to rape then no, it's not a suitable read for a 12 year old boy. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
