<div id="review_1650674325" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1650674325" />
    <a title="Carol" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7668522-carol"><img alt="Carol" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546364878p2/7668522.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1650674325?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol" href="/user/show/7668522-carol">Carol</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781605981291" href="/book/show/7921091-this-perfect-day">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7668522-carol?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7668522-carol?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7668522-carol?shelf=read-2016">read-2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1650674325" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4323929126931700549">Completed <u>way</u> back in June, 1969, Ira Levin&apos;s novel <b>THIS PERFECT DAY</b> introduces a futuristic colony with a computer at the helm where <b>everyone</b> is programmed to be cold and lifeless, and <b>everyone,</b> as a member of the &quot;family&quot; is monitored throughout the day.<p>
  <i>&quot;Even the basic facts of nature are subject to the Unicomp&apos;s will ----- men do not grow facial hair, women do not develop breasts, and it only rains at night.&quot;</i>
</p><p>Lots of action and some pretty cool twists along the way keep things from becomin</p></span>
  <span id="freeText4323929126931700549" style="display:none">Completed <u>way</u> back in June, 1969, Ira Levin's novel <b>THIS PERFECT DAY</b> introduces a futuristic colony with a computer at the helm where <b>everyone</b> is programmed to be cold and lifeless, and <b>everyone,</b> as a member of the "family" is monitored throughout the day.<p>
  <i>"Even the basic facts of nature are subject to the Unicomp's will ----- men do not grow facial hair, women do not develop breasts, and it only rains at night."</i>
</p><p>Lots of action and some pretty cool twists along the way keep things from becoming too dulled or normalized as Chip aka Li RM35M4419 with his one green eye, and a few of his witty non-conforming pals, have some different views on the subject.</p><p>GREAT sci-fi Classic!</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="4323929126931700549" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


