<div id="review_115846480" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/115846480" />
    <a title="Heather Crews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4126011-heather-crews"><img alt="Heather Crews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598083968p2/4126011.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/115846480?book_show_action=true">Aug 08, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heather Crews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heather Crews" href="/user/show/4126011-heather-crews">Heather Crews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9780062357755" href="/book/show/20896081-this-perfect-day">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4126011-heather-crews?shelf=horror-occult-supernatural-fiction">horror-occult-supernatural-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4126011-heather-crews?shelf=classics-tasty-fiction-of-every-var">classics-tasty-fiction-of-every-var</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer115846480" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2903403541095866638">This is one of my absolute favorite books of all time. Do yourself and favor and read it if you haven&apos;t before. I pick it up and reread it every couple of years, and I think I always notice something new in the story....but that may just be because my view on life changes over the years, and thus I come at it from a different approach. <br/>It is very much in the vein of other books that deal with the concept of a futuristic dystopian world, i.e, Brave New World, 1984, and Logan&apos;s Run. <br/>It was out OOP</span>
  <span id="freeText2903403541095866638" style="display:none">This is one of my absolute favorite books of all time. Do yourself and favor and read it if you haven't before. I pick it up and reread it every couple of years, and I think I always notice something new in the story....but that may just be because my view on life changes over the years, and thus I come at it from a different approach. <br>It is very much in the vein of other books that deal with the concept of a futuristic dystopian world, i.e, Brave New World, 1984, and Logan's Run. <br>It was out OOP for several years, and after reading (and losing) my mother's copy when I was a teenager....I scoured used books stores for YEARS before I finally stumbled on a paperback version. A few years later, I also came across an original first run hardcover edition from 1970. It is one of my favorite possessions. :D<br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/760546.This_Perfect_Day" title="This Perfect Day by Ira Levin" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/photo.goodreads.com/books/1223537367s/760546.jpg" alt="This Perfect Day by Ira Levin" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a></span>
