<span id="freeTextContainer15399623155737639120">What makes This Perfect Day a must read is the depth of the main character. The author reveals him to us gradually -- as the character becomes less drugged/more cogent, we know and care about him even more. The scanners and bracelets remind me of the RFID cards and readers we have today, slightly disturbing. The world development was interesting enough to explore and give thought to. One of the better dystopian novels I&apos;ve read</span>
  <span id="freeText15399623155737639120" style="display:none">What makes This Perfect Day a must read is the depth of the main character. The author reveals him to us gradually -- as the character becomes less drugged/more cogent, we know and care about him even more. The scanners and bracelets remind me of the RFID cards and readers we have today, slightly disturbing. The world development was interesting enough to explore and give thought to. One of the better dystopian novels I've read</span>
