<span id="freeTextContainer1498711220651643470">An excellent read. A deceptively simple writing style belies a very complex book with deep social commentary. The question is simple. What happens when a computer runs the world and keeps the citizenry asleep and suddenly you wake up? Social commentary on over medication, individuality, collectivism, as well as hard choices make for a very entertaining read. Oddly enough, I think <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/139390.This_Perfect_Day' title='This Perfect Day by Ira Levin' rel='nofollow noopener'>This Perfect Day</a> is more relevant today than it was even 45 years ago.</span>
  <span id="freeText1498711220651643470" style="display:none">An excellent read. A deceptively simple writing style belies a very complex book with deep social commentary. The question is simple. What happens when a computer runs the world and keeps the citizenry asleep and suddenly you wake up? Social commentary on over medication, individuality, collectivism, as well as hard choices make for a very entertaining read. Oddly enough, I think <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/139390.This_Perfect_Day" title="This Perfect Day by Ira Levin" rel="nofollow noopener">This Perfect Day</a> is more relevant today than it was even 45 years ago.</span>
